---
import Layout from '@/components/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout 
  title="Start a Ruck Club - Step-by-Step Guide" 
  description="Step-by-step guide to starting a ruck club. Build your crew from the ground up with proven strategies."
>
  <div class="bg-surface py-16">
    <div class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      <!-- Header Section -->
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h1 class="text-4xl font-heading text-secondary mb-4 bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded">START A CLUB</h1>
        <p class="text-lg font-serif text-muted-foreground max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Building a crew from scratch takes effort, but the rewards are worth it. Here's how to launch a ruck club that lasts.
        </p>
      </div>

    <!-- Before You Start -->
    <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded mb-4">Before You Start</h2>
      <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
        <p>Answer these questions before launching:</p>
        <ul class="space-y-2 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>What's your purpose?</strong> Fitness? Community? Wellness? Competition? Define your purpose.</li>
          <li><strong>Who's your audience?</strong> Veterans? Beginners? Professionals? Families? Know who you're recruiting.</li>
          <li><strong>What's your capacity?</strong> Start small. You can grow later, but don't overcommit early.</li>
          <li><strong>What's the commitment level?</strong> Weekly? Bi-weekly? Monthly? Set expectations from day one.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- The Launch Checklist -->
    <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded mb-6">Launch Checklist</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <!-- Phase 1 -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Phase 1: Foundation (Weeks 1-2)</h3>
          <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal list-inside text-muted">
            <li>Define your club's purpose, values, and target audience</li>
            <li>Choose a working name and identity</li>
            <li>Research local areas for safe, accessible ruck routes</li>
            <li>Set a regular meeting schedule (pick a day and time that works)</li>
            <li>Establish basic safety guidelines and equipment recommendations</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Phase 2 -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Phase 2: Outreach (Weeks 2-3)</h3>
          <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal list-inside text-muted">
            <li>Create a communication channel (Discord, WhatsApp, Facebook group, or email list)</li>
            <li>Spread the word through social media, local running stores, gyms, and veteran networks</li>
            <li>Design simple promotional materials or graphics</li>
            <li>Reach out to potential founding members (3-5 committed people minimum)</li>
            <li>Plan your launch ruck with a beginner-friendly route</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Phase 3 -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Phase 3: Launch (Week 3-4)</h3>
          <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal list-inside text-muted">
            <li>Host your first "founding ruck" — keep it short (1-2 miles) and easy</li>
            <li>Collect feedback from attendees immediately after</li>
            <li>Set expectations for future rucks (pace, weight, format)</li>
            <li>Establish a recurring schedule</li>
            <li>Celebrate your launch and thank founding members</li>
          </ol>
        </div>

        <!-- Phase 4 -->
        <div class="border-l-4 border-primary pl-6">
          <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-4 text-foreground">Phase 4: Growth (Month 2+)</h3>
          <ol class="space-y-3 list-decimal list-inside text-muted">
            <li>Consistently show up — reliability builds trust</li>
            <li>Welcome new members and assign mentors</li>
            <li>Create traditions (special rucks, end-of-season celebrations)</li>
            <li>Document your club's story and share it</li>
            <li>Iterate based on member feedback</li>
          </ol>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Common Mistakes -->
    <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded mb-4">Common Mistakes to Avoid</h2>
      <div class="grid gap-4 md:grid-cols-2">
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">Going Too Fast, Too Soon</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Start with easy rucks. Many new clubs burn out by making first rucks too hard.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">No Clear Schedule</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Random scheduling kills momentum. Pick a regular day/time and stick to it.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">Ignoring Beginners</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Beginners build the club. If they don't return, neither does growth.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="bg-red-50 rounded-lg p-5 border border-red-200">
          <h3 class="font-bold mb-2 text-red-700">No Communication System</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-red-600">Without a clear way to share updates, members drift away.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Leadership Tips -->
    <section class="mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-2xl font-heading text-secondary bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded mb-4">Leadership Tips for New Club Founders</h2>
      <div class="prose lg:prose-xl max-w-none">
        <ul class="space-y-3 list-disc list-inside">
          <li><strong>Serve first, lead second.</strong> Your job is to make others successful, not to be the star.</li>
          <li><strong>Delegate early.</strong> Give members ownership of specific responsibilities.</li>
          <li><strong>Rotate leadership.</strong> Others should eventually lead rucks, not just you.</li>
          <li><strong>Document everything.</strong> Write down routes, lessons learned, and member info.</li>
          <li><strong>Stay humble.</strong> You don't need to be the fittest — you need to be reliable.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Resources -->
    <section class="mb-12">
      <div class="bg-muted-50 rounded-lg p-6 border border-muted-200">
          <h2 class="text-xl font-heading text-secondary bg-[#8a1e1e] text-white px-3 py-2 rounded mb-4">Downloadable Resources</h2>
        <p class="text-muted mb-4">Print these checklists to help with your club launch:</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a href="/checklists/start-a-club.pdf" class="btn btn-primary" download>
            Download Club Starter Checklist (PDF)
          </a>
          <a href="/checklists/what-is-a-ruck-club.pdf" class="btn btn-secondary" download>
            Download What is a Ruck Club (PDF)
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Navigation -->
    <nav class="flex gap-4">
      <a href="/lead/ruck-clubs" class="btn btn-secondary">
        ← Back to Ruck Clubs
      </a>
      <a href="/lead/ruck-clubs/leadership-principles" class="btn btn-utility">
        Leadership Principles →
      </a>
    </nav>
    </div>
  </div>
</Layout>
